metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #509
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Fit #6
metadata.description:
Inspired by Joe Jackson's song "Fit" (1980), this Tezos params project is my gift to all my collectors. 

If you own one of my projects on ETH, you will also get a free reserve slot on August 1st - but you must create an account on fxhash before then.

metadata.name: Pixel Spaceships Solos #293
metadata.description:
"Pixel Spaceships Solos" is retro pixel pop art.  It is a further exploration of the original "Pixel Spaceships" project, focused more on single ships rather than mass composition of ships.  "Solos" also offers a second-chance to explore some of the more esoteric features that may not have been fully explored during the original mint (and all such probabilities have been increased here).

Further write-up:  https://www.davebollinger.us/pixelspaceships

Note:  First set of reserves are only for minters of original "Pixel Spaceships", remaining reserves will be released after that.

EXPECTED FEATURE RARITY, approximately (#variations):
  Polarity:  75% positive/on-white, 25% negative/on-black
  Ship Shading:  33% mono(2), 33% gray(2), 33% color(6)
  Ship Gridded:  70% none, 30% gridded
  Panel Shading:  10% none, 45% gray, 45% color
  Panel Gridded:  70% none, 30% gridded
  Trace Shading:  10% none, 30% dark, 30% light, 30% color
  Edge Type:  50% no-edge/full-bleed, 50% edged(12)
  Edge Shading:  50% match polarity, 50% opposite polarity (also used by vignette)
  Vignette Type:  12% vignetted(3) (overrides edge type above)
  Vignette Amount:  33% light, 33% moderate, 33% strong
  Warp Panel:  12% warped (varies from mild to extreme, weighted toward mild)
  Warp Trace:  10% warped (varies from mild to extreme, weighted toward mild)
  Warp Ship:  8% warped (varies from mild to extreme, weighted toward mild)
  Extra Large: 8% xlarge (less suitable for most PFP uses)
  Double Glitch: 7% glitched
  Overscan Glitch: 6% glitched (unaffected by edge/vignette)
  Battle Glitch:  5% glitched (unaffected by edge/vignette)
  Explosion Shading:  33% mono, 33% gray, 33% color
  Escape Pod: 4% have pod
  Most features are not mututally exclusive and can occur in any combination unless noted above.

CONTROLS:

Press 's' to save the image.

Press a number key to adjust internal resolution (do this prior to saving):
  '1' : 1024px x 1024px
  '2' : 2048px x 2048px
  '3' : 4096px x 4096px
  '4' : 8192px x 8192px

metadata.name: MOMENT #29
metadata.description:
An endless row of them making up each life. Some poignant, some inspiring, some grievous, some affirming - but most of them a tad boring, a bit generic, almost forgettable like bland fabric. How can a life constructed from such mundanity count for anything? Maybe thanks to the last one, the one that stitches them all together, like a punchline to an absurdist joke.

Generative art written in JavaScript + Canvas with a little bit of help from p5.js.

An experiment in gradient- and shading techniques, and restrictions of a flow field.
Written in JavaScript for Canvas.

metadata.name: Tintinnabulum #60
metadata.description:
An audiovisual collection.
.
Click to start the sound.
..
Tintinnabulum is an endless generative music player.
...
There are 8 color palettes which correlate with 8 different root notes (C, G, F, D, Bb, A, Eb, B).

5 Noise types correlate with 5 different scales (Minor, Hicaz, Major, Lydian, Locrian) which have 2 registers.

2 different rhythmical structures (Polyrhthmic & standart). Each has 4 divisions.

2 rotation options; On, Off.
....
Harmonization process based on Avro Part's 'Tintinnabuli' style.

Made with p5.js and Web Audio.

Ilgın İçözü, November 2021
@distcollective

metadata.name: Insula #42
metadata.description:
An audiovisual collection.
.
Click to start the sound.
..
Insula is an endless generative music player.
...
There are 6 different grid size; 4 squares and 20 squares are the rare ones.

2 different background texture; Lines, Grain.

2 different color placement; Circular, Linear.

7 different noise types.

8 different scales with fixed root notes; C Maj., C Lydian, D Dorian, D Min. Penta., G Maj., G Maj. Penta., F Mixolydian, F Min.

2 different rhythmical structures; 2:3, 4:5.

2 different note indicator style; Circle and Square. Square is rare and behaves differently.

5 different note indicator line divisions.
....
Harmonization process based on Avro Part's 'Tintinnabuli' style.

Grid design inspired from Novation's Launchpad.


Made with p5.js and Web Audio.

Ilgın İçözü, December 2021
@distcollective

metadata.name: Voice #209
metadata.description: This series highlights the unique, authentic, and valuable voice that we all have. We should strive to discover, hone, and leverage it. Generative art made by Devi Parikh (https://twitter.com/deviparikh).
